1
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:14,167
<i> Emma?</i>

2
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:17,333
<i>If possible, please don't tell
anyone the patient is here.</i>

3
00:00:17,467 --> 00:00:18,767
<i> Okay, Logan.</i>

4
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:20,467
<i>That's also how it was with
Jade.</i>

5
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:23,167
<i> You love saving women.</i>

6
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:24,100
<i> How are you?</i>

7
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:25,833
<i> Who are you? I don't know you!</i>

8
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:29,933
<i>The man who helped you escape
from the yakuza in Japan.</i>

9
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:31,500
<i> Oh, no, Madam.</i>

10
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:33,733
<i> Danilo's here.</i>

11
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:36,233
<i>Tell him Emma escaped
on her own will.</i>

12
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:38,567
<i>And she has no intention
of seeing them.</i>

13
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,400
<i> She said you didn't want her.</i>

14
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>That's why she wanted
to go away.</i>

15
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:46,533
<i>That means Mom doesn't want us
anymore.</i>

16
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:49,567
<i>I'm ready to fill in Emma's
shortcomings with you</i>

17
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:50,800
<i> and Mookie.</i>

18
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:54,100
<i>Even if it means that I have
to be Mookie's mother.</i>

19
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:55,733
<i> I'll help you, Danilo.</i>

20
00:02:28,033 --> 00:02:30,967
<i>You promised me you
wouldn't be like Mommy.</i>

21
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,733
<i>You told me you wouldn't hurt
me.</i>

22
00:02:34,733 --> 00:02:38,367
<i>You said you wouldn't leave me,
no matter what happens.</i>

23
00:02:38,500 --> 00:02:39,700
<i> But what did you do?</i>

24
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:46,067
<i>You shouldn't have looked for me
if you would only leave us.</i>

25
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,500
<i> I wish I hadn't met you.</i>

26
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:50,400
<i> I don't want you anymore, Mom.</i>

27
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:52,400
<i> I don't want to see you again!</i>

28
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:01,100
<i> I don't want to see you again!</i>

29
00:03:01,233 --> 00:03:03,567
<i> I don't want to see you again!</i>

30
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,400
<i>I hope you don't come back
anymore!</i>

31
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:06,900
Mookie!

32
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:08,000
Mookie?

33
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:09,000
Mookie?

34
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,267
Mookie!

35
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,367
Mookie!

36
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,600
Mookie, dear!

37
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,400
Mookie!

38
00:03:18,533 --> 00:03:20,400
Mookie!

39
00:03:20,567 --> 00:03:22,933
- Mookie, dear! Where are you?
- Son of a...

40
00:03:24,233 --> 00:03:25,167
Mookie!

41
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,967
You haven't recovered yet.
Go get some rest.

42
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:28,467
Let go of me!

43
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,233
You need to rest!

44
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:33,100
My daughter needs me!
She's in danger!

45
00:03:33,233 --> 00:03:35,133
Your daughter isn't here!
Come on! Get some rest.

46
00:03:35,267 --> 00:03:37,900
Mookie! Mookie!

47
00:03:40,567 --> 00:03:41,400
That's enough.

48
00:04:22,467 --> 00:04:24,533
You're lucky I found you.

49
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,267
Poor you.

50
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:32,433
No one seems to care for you.

51
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:36,600
Don't worry.

52
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,400
I'll help you.

53
00:04:41,033 --> 00:04:42,200
I'll take care of you.

54
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,800
Wait, wait.
Jade, Jade!

55
00:04:56,933 --> 00:04:57,500
Jade.

56
00:04:59,267 --> 00:05:01,200
We shouldn't be doing this.

57
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:05,500
This is wrong.

58
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:08,133
We shouldn't do this.

59
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:10,333
Don't you like me, Danilo?

60
00:05:10,467 --> 00:05:12,500
Because I like you a lot.

61
00:05:12,633 --> 00:05:14,200
Please accept me.

62
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:18,400
Emma?

63
00:05:35,733 --> 00:05:37,267
Logan, here's the food.

64
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:39,700
Please put it over there,
Manang.

65
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:40,767
Okay.

66
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,100
- You can go.
- Okay.

67
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:02,467
You're awake.

68
00:06:07,133 --> 00:06:08,300
You're safe here.

69
00:06:10,367 --> 00:06:13,400
Go on and eat.
Regain your strength.

70
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:15,167
Then, I'll give you
your medicine.

71
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,633
I don't want to take any
medicines.

72
00:06:17,767 --> 00:06:19,000
I'm not taking it!

73
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:20,033
No, no.

74
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,200
This isn't the wrong medication.

75
00:06:23,700 --> 00:06:25,000
This will help you get better.

76
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,533
Don't worry.

77
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,900
You won't get harmed.

78
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:36,100
I'll help you get better.

79
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:18,267
Danilo.

80
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,067
Jade!

81
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,300
Jade, sorry.

82
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:22,133
Sorry.

83
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:25,000
This is my fault.

84
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:26,000
Jade.

85
00:07:26,133 --> 00:07:27,433
No, no, no, Danilo.

86
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:29,800
It's my fault.

87
00:07:31,067 --> 00:07:32,767
It's my fault that...

88
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:37,867
I don't know how it happened.

89
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:44,133
I'm such a bad sister.
I'm so sorry.

90
00:07:56,967 --> 00:07:58,767
I'm so sorry, Danilo.

91
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:10,267
I shouldn't have done this!

92
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,567
Forgive me, Emma.

93
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,567
I hope you can forgive me, Emma.

94
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,567
Bastards.

95
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:38,867
You're so big, but you let
a drunk man knock you down.

96
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,867
What's your salary for?

97
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:47,267
If this happens again,
I will knock you down myself.

98
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,800
I'm sorry, Boss.

99
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:51,567
Sorry, my foot.
What are you blabbering?

100
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:53,433
What nonsense are you talking
about?

101
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,700
What can your sorry do?

102
00:08:58,067 --> 00:09:01,000
Get out of here
before I beat you.

103
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,033
Stupid.

104
00:09:10,567 --> 00:09:11,800
Boss.

105
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:13,200
Yes, Marco.

106
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:17,833
Any updates on Mr. Uy?

107
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:21,367
He hasn't paid his debt yet.

108
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,667
He hasn't even given me
the interest.

109
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,333
He asked for an extension again,
Boss.

110
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:29,767
My lending business will go
bankrupt if this continues.

111
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:34,233
What about the thing I told you
to investigate?

112
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:35,967
That's why I'm here, Boss.

113
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:39,767
I got information about
the woman you're helping.

114
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:43,800
What is it?

115
00:09:43,933 --> 00:09:46,533
I paid someone in Haven Wood.

116
00:09:46,667 --> 00:09:50,367
But she could only give me
a little information.

117
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,333
The woman's name is Emma Joseco.

118
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:58,500
Emma Joseco.

119
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:01,600
Emma.

120
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:06,833
I heard she's married
and has a child.

121
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:11,400
But I don't have any information
about the two.

122
00:10:11,533 --> 00:10:14,100
The people I asked around
are scared.

123
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:18,900
Doctor Samson said they
probably gave her

124
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:22,600
the wrong medication
in Haven Wood.

125
00:10:25,633 --> 00:10:27,067
You're doing it right.

126
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,733
Continue investigating.

127
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:32,933
I want to get to know
that woman better.

128
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,400
Emma.

129
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:53,633
As I said, the patient's
withdrawal symptoms

130
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:56,600
from the medication she received
won't go away quickly.

131
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:05,167
Are you sure it's alright
with you that she's here?

132
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,800
Yes, Doc.

133
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:15,867
Taking care of a psychiatric
patient isn't easy, Logan.

134
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:20,867
And I can't promise you
I can treat her fast.

135
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:30,600
Why don't you transfer her
to another psychiatric center?

136
00:11:39,533 --> 00:11:40,733
Okay.

137
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:41,900
I have to go.

138
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:43,833
I need to do my rounds
in the hospital.

139
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:45,733
Thank you, Doc.

140
00:11:48,833 --> 00:11:50,000
Be safe, Doc.

141
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:54,267
Please don't bring me back
to Haven Wood.

142
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:57,133
They're making me crazy.
I won't get better there.

143
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:02,667
On one condition...

144
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:09,333
You'll cooperate
with the treatment.

145
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:12,633
You'll trust me.

146
00:12:12,767 --> 00:12:13,933
And most of all,

147
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:18,400
you'll eat and get stronger.

148
00:12:21,733 --> 00:12:22,833
Let me.

149
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:27,533
Today...

150
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:32,567
Soup, fish, rice, juice...

151
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:39,800
You don't want it?

152
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:43,133
Okay.

153
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,267
Hello, Haven Wood.

154
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:52,533
Yes, I'm sending a patient
there.

155
00:12:52,667 --> 00:12:55,367
Maybe it'll take 30 minutes...

156
00:12:59,567 --> 00:13:01,267
Never mind.

157
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,200
These are some of the
foods I learned to cook

158
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:25,700
when I was still in Japan.

159
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:29,300
But I'm worried about
you getting tired of my cooking,

160
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:32,200
so let's eat out.

161
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,033
Let's go somewhere.

162
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:35,333
Really?

163
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,833
Don't worry, Mookie.

164
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:44,300
Even though your mom isn't here,
I'm here.

165
00:13:44,433 --> 00:13:45,800
I was also a mom.

166
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:53,433
I mean, I tried taking care
of my friends' kids in Japan.

167
00:13:55,233 --> 00:14:00,700
I can't promise I'll be as good
as your Mommy Emma.

168
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:05,333
But I'll try my very best
to take good care of you

169
00:14:05,467 --> 00:14:07,000
and your dad.

170
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:11,967
So, I hope you'll also treat me
as your mom, baby girl.

171
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,433
Is that okay?

172
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:19,500
Auntie Jade, thank you.

173
00:14:19,633 --> 00:14:23,300
I don't know what to do without
you.

174
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,467
Anything for you, baby girl.

175
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,967
Let's eat!
The food will get cold. Come on.

176
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:32,667
Yeah. The food you cooked
is good.

177
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,167
Try the gyoza.

178
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,367
You can go now.

179
00:15:00,767 --> 00:15:02,133
It's normal.

180
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:04,533
The doctor said
it's withdrawal symptoms

181
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:06,333
from the wrong medicines
you took.

182
00:15:12,633 --> 00:15:14,467
Why are you helping me?

183
00:15:15,667 --> 00:15:17,333
Because you need it.

184
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:21,133
I found you unconscious
on the street.

185
00:15:21,267 --> 00:15:25,333
Anyone would do what I did.

186
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:28,767
But if you don't trust me,

187
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,967
please tell me where you live.

188
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:33,900
I'll have someone bring you
home.

189
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:37,100
I don't think there's a family
that wants me.

190
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:41,400
They even let me be brought
to a psychiatric center.

191
00:15:42,833 --> 00:15:45,900
I can't blame them
because I hurt them.

192
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:51,600
I feel like they don't want me
anymore.

193
00:15:52,733 --> 00:15:55,200
Because they never came back
to Haven Wood to see me.

194
00:15:56,567 --> 00:15:59,433
But I really have a bad feeling
about Jade.

195
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:02,133
Wait.

196
00:16:04,067 --> 00:16:04,833
Jade?

197
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:07,900
Jade Caparas.

198
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:12,533
I just found out that we're
sisters.

199
00:16:14,533 --> 00:16:18,400
But I have a bad feeling about
her.

200
00:16:18,533 --> 00:16:21,200
I know she's the same as her
twin, Olive.

201
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,467
<i> Where are you going?</i>

202
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,967
<i> What's this?</i>

203
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,100
<i> Mookie!</i>

204
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:36,300
<i> Danilo!</i>

205
00:16:37,367 --> 00:16:38,833
<i> Mookie!</i>

206
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:41,133
I don't trust Jade Caparas.

207
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:42,600
She's planning something bad
against me.

208
00:16:42,733 --> 00:16:43,767
She'll kill me.

209
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:45,733
She'll kill me.

210
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:47,767
She'll kill me.

211
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,333
She'll kill me

212
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,300
Emma.

213
00:17:00,667 --> 00:17:01,933
I'll touch you, okay?

214
00:17:02,367 --> 00:17:03,633
I'll be gentle.

215
00:17:09,033 --> 00:17:10,033
I'm here.

216
00:17:12,167 --> 00:17:13,667
Trust me.

217
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,833
You need to regain
your strength.

218
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:21,600
Because once you recover,
we'll go and see your child.

219
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:23,767
I promise you that.

220
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,433
They'll just bring you back
to Haven Wood if you do it now.

221
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:30,367
Do you want that?

222
00:17:32,633 --> 00:17:33,367
No, right?

223
00:17:34,933 --> 00:17:36,667
I'll help you bounce back.

224
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,667
Just trust me.

225
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:47,667
So, for now, get some rest.

226
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:49,933
Get stronger.

227
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,300
I'll just take this call.

228
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:21,333
Marco, what's up?

229
00:18:42,967 --> 00:18:44,433
Go on and eat.

230
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:47,767
- Baby girl, come on and eat.
- I will, Auntie.

231
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:54,200
Auntie, I'm sorry you've
had to take care of us.

232
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:55,400
Yeah, Jade.

233
00:18:55,567 --> 00:18:58,600
What you've done for us
is more than enough.

234
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:01,233
It's okay.

235
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:05,367
Actually, in a way,
you two make me happy.

236
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:10,567
Because it's my dream
to have my own family.

237
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:15,000
I didn't feel the love from my
and Jade's adoptive parents.

238
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:17,800
I mean Olive.

239
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:27,567
That's why I told myself I'd do
everything once I had a family.

240
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:32,300
Eat, baby girl.

241
00:19:40,033 --> 00:19:41,567
Son of a gun!

242
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,433
So, Emma's telling the truth.

243
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:48,133
She's not only connected
to Jade.

244
00:19:48,267 --> 00:19:50,100
She's her sister.

245
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:54,000
Based on the information
I gathered, Jade's twin sister,

246
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:58,733
Olive Caparas, stole Emma
and Danilo's daughter.

247
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:02,433
That's why the kid is still
using Olive Caparas's name.

248
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:06,800
Olive and Emma share
the same mother.

249
00:20:07,967 --> 00:20:10,433
But I heard Olive Caparas
is already dead.

250
00:20:12,867 --> 00:20:14,767
So Jade has a twin sister.

251
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:18,200
Looks like fate is playing
tricks on you, Boss.

252
00:20:20,533 --> 00:20:24,367
But it seems that you're already
falling for Emma.

253
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,933
Unfortunately, she's no longer
available.

254
00:20:27,067 --> 00:20:28,500
She has a husband.

255
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:34,633
Are you sure it's Emma's
husband?

256
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,100
Yes, Boss.

257
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:38,467
The man's name is Danilo.

258
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:40,533
And Mookie is the kid's name.

259
00:20:42,267 --> 00:20:43,900
Dan, wait.

260
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:53,833
I didn't notice I was being
messy.

261
00:20:53,967 --> 00:20:55,333
- Sorry.
- Keep eating.

262
00:20:58,700 --> 00:21:00,100
Dan, wait.

263
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:10,000
I didn't notice I was being
messy.

264
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:11,467
- Sorry.
- Keep eating.

265
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:13,867
Look, Boss.

266
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:17,367
Jade seems to like the father.

267
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:19,533
Look how she cares for them.

268
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:27,167
I don't care if it's the man
Jade is going crazy for.

269
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:31,133
What matters to me now is Emma.

270
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:37,933
Do you mean you won't tell
them that you have Emma?

271
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:43,300
We don't know the whole story
yet.

272
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:46,833
Emma should stay with me
for now.

273
00:21:48,133 --> 00:21:53,000
Is that really the reason
you're helping Emma?

274
00:21:53,133 --> 00:21:55,967
Aren't you falling
for her already?

275
00:22:07,933 --> 00:22:12,467
After six months of
dedicated treatment,

276
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,867
therapy, and perseverance,
you're now healed.

277
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,367
Well, what can I say?

278
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:19,567
I'm not surprised.

279
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:21,533
Thank you, Logan.

280
00:22:21,667 --> 00:22:23,400
Thank you so much.

281
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:26,833
This is the only time I've
felt like having a whole

282
00:22:26,967 --> 00:22:28,133
and happy family.

283
00:22:28,267 --> 00:22:33,233
Danilo and Mookie fulfill
that dream of mine.

284
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:34,600
I wonder how they're doing.

285
00:22:34,733 --> 00:22:35,900
I wonder how my husband
and child are doing.

286
00:22:36,033 --> 00:22:37,633
Can I see them?

287
00:22:37,767 --> 00:22:39,267
I don't think it's
the right time.

288
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,933
But I'm okay now, Logan.

289
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:42,300
I'm healed.

290
00:22:42,433 --> 00:22:43,933
I miss them so much.

291
00:22:44,067 --> 00:22:48,100
Dan, will you take this journey
with me?

292
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:52,000
Will you let the two of us
and Mookie be a family?

293
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:56,867
Mom?
